  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rio+20 2013: IUCN - Closing the knowledge-investment gap in drylands</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This initiative will demonstrate dryland investment opportunities, galvanise action to leverage investment in target countries, and develop tools and approaches that can be replicated in other developing countries and with other development partners. Drylands occypy 41% of the earth&apos;s terrestrial area, yet dryland management is a low investment area but still with substantial potential. The initiative will target two principal results: 1. Investment options identified through multi-stakeholder consultations and application of IUCN assessement tools and knowledge products. 2. Investment options prioritized, resources mobilised and opportunities piloted to enhance capacity for policy implementation.</narrative>
  </description>
